Fixes: #9645 Account for startup-time chunk exclusion in ChunkAppend cost estimation. Previously, when a query restriction couldn't be folded at plan time (e.g. a stable timestamptz->timestamp cast on a parameter), the planner had to keep all chunks in the plan and defer pruning to executor startup. ChunkAppend's row estimate then summed over all chunks, which cascaded into bad sizing for upstream HashAggregates, joins, and sorts. The estimate now uses estimate_expression_value() to predict which chunks will survive startup exclusion and scales the ChunkAppend row estimate accordingly. The actual plan still contains all chunks; runtime startup exclusion remains the mechanism that enforces correctness.
